# Array -

Array is collection of element in contiguous memory locations ,
array can store multiple types of data

let arr = [1,2,3,4,5]

console.log(arr[3]) // accessing element in array

arr[0] = 10  // modifing element in array

console.log(arr)

console.log(arr.length)  // length of array

# Tranversal in Array

1. for loop in array

for(let i ; i < arr.length ; i++){
	console.log(arr[9])
}

2. forEach in array

arr.forEach(item => console.log(item))

3. for...of in array

for(let item of arr){
	console.log(item)
}

# Insertion in Array

1. Insertion at begining

arr.push(20)

2. Insertion at End

arr.unshift(90)

3. Insertion at Specific Position 

arr.splice(3,0,10) (index , delete , new )

# Deletion in Array

1. Deletion at Begining

arr.shift() -- time Complixity O(n) because all other element are shifted

2. Deletion at End 

arr.pop()

3. Deletion at Specific Position

arr.splice(3,0)

